INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (37,1,'2023-10-08 19:05:25','2023-10-08 19:05:25','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">GUIDING CLIENTS THROUGH THE PROBATE PROCESS</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Probate is a court process through which a deceased persons assets are distributed to beneficiaries. In general, the probate process consists of:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Taking an inventory of the estates assets</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Determining whether there is a valid will</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Paying the deceased persons debts and other expenses</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Distributing the remaining assets to the appropriate beneficiaries</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The probate process occurs at a difficult time, while people are grieving. But, probate administration does not have to be overwhelming. With more than 40 years of experience,&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group&nbsp;guides families through probate in a cost-effective and efficient manner. The firm has Maryland office locations in Bethesda and Silver Spring, as well as an office in Washington, D.C., to meet with clients from all of the surrounding areas, including Montgomery County, Prince Georges County and northern Virginia.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is wise to avoid probate when possible. Avoiding probate saves money, allows for a quicker transfer of assets to beneficiaries and prevents your familys assets and debts from becoming public record. Probate can be prevented during the estate planning process, typically by implementing&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/trusts/\">trusts</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Susan Eleff&nbsp;understands that probate is a sensitive and emotional time for clients. The firm works closely and compassionately with the personal representatives of estates to help them efficiently manage the entire probate administration process.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is important to seek legal guidance as soon as possible in the probate process. If you take steps before you completely understand your legal obligations and rights, you may make irreparable mistakes regarding tax, title and creditor issues, among other things. For example, if you would like to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/wills/\">disclaim an asset</a>, you will not be able to do so if you have already spent or used any of it. This is just one pitfall that must be avoided.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Get Help With Probate</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you are probating an estate, it is important to seek legal guidance early in the process. Selecting a probate attorney can be highly personal and&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;recognizes this. She and her legal team provide potential clients with initial consultations free of charge so that they can get to know the firm and decide whether it is the right fit. Call&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:+1-800-765-2662\">800-765-2662</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/contact/\">fill out this form</a>&nbsp;to schedule your *free legal consultation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>*Certain limitations may apply.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Probate','','publish','closed','closed','','probate','','','2023-10-08 19:05:25','2023-10-08 19:05:25','',20,'http://elefflaw.local/?page_id=37',0,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (38,1,'2023-10-08 19:05:25','2023-10-08 19:05:25','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">GUIDING CLIENTS THROUGH THE PROBATE PROCESS</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Probate is a court process through which a deceased persons assets are distributed to beneficiaries. In general, the probate process consists of:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Taking an inventory of the estates assets</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Determining whether there is a valid will</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Paying the deceased persons debts and other expenses</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Distributing the remaining assets to the appropriate beneficiaries</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The probate process occurs at a difficult time, while people are grieving. But, probate administration does not have to be overwhelming. With more than 40 years of experience,&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group&nbsp;guides families through probate in a cost-effective and efficient manner. The firm has Maryland office locations in Bethesda and Silver Spring, as well as an office in Washington, D.C., to meet with clients from all of the surrounding areas, including Montgomery County, Prince Georges County and northern Virginia.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is wise to avoid probate when possible. Avoiding probate saves money, allows for a quicker transfer of assets to beneficiaries and prevents your familys assets and debts from becoming public record. Probate can be prevented during the estate planning process, typically by implementing&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/trusts/\">trusts</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Susan Eleff&nbsp;understands that probate is a sensitive and emotional time for clients. The firm works closely and compassionately with the personal representatives of estates to help them efficiently manage the entire probate administration process.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is important to seek legal guidance as soon as possible in the probate process. If you take steps before you completely understand your legal obligations and rights, you may make irreparable mistakes regarding tax, title and creditor issues, among other things. For example, if you would like to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/wills/\">disclaim an asset</a>, you will not be able to do so if you have already spent or used any of it. This is just one pitfall that must be avoided.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Get Help With Probate</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you are probating an estate, it is important to seek legal guidance early in the process. Selecting a probate attorney can be highly personal and&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;recognizes this. She and her legal team provide potential clients with initial consultations free of charge so that they can get to know the firm and decide whether it is the right fit. Call&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:+1-800-765-2662\">800-765-2662</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/contact/\">fill out this form</a>&nbsp;to schedule your *free legal consultation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>*Certain limitations may apply.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Probate','','inherit','closed','closed','','37-revision-v1','','','2023-10-08 19:05:25','2023-10-08 19:05:25','',37,'http://elefflaw.local/?p=38',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (39,1,'2023-10-08 19:06:01','2023-10-08 19:06:01','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">QUESTIONS THAT ARE FREQUENTLY ASKED ABOUT ESTATE PLANNING</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Taking the first step toward planning for the future can be challenging. Attorney&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;and her team at&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group&nbsp;can help you understand all your options and make the process easier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Below are some questions that the firms clients often&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/\">ask about estate planning</a>. To discuss your specific needs and concerns, call the firm at&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:+1-800-765-2662\">800-765-2662</a>&nbsp;or contact Susan online. Consultations at our office locations in Bethesda, Silver Spring and Washington D.C. are free with certain limitations. Susan serves individuals in Prince George County, Montgomery County,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Do I need a will?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is no requirement that anyone have a will in place. However, it is in your best interests to have a legally binding will that details how you wish your estate to be handled and distributed upon your death. If you die without a will, the state will take over, and the estate will be distributed according to state law by the courts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Who can benefit from a trust?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is a myth that only the wealthy benefit from establishing trusts as part of their estate plans. A trust can help anyone who is seeking ways to protect their assets and property for their future use and the benefit of their heirs and beneficiaries. A trust can be not only a place for assets to be collected and protected but also a way to avoid estate taxes and probate. There are many different types of trusts that achieve different goals. Talking through your situation with your attorney is the best way to determine which trust is right for you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Can an estate plan help me avoid estate taxes?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A carefully crafted estate plan may help you legally avoid some estate taxes through asset management, gifting and other means. However, even the most comprehensive estate plan cannot exclude every possibility of estate taxes being applied. Your attorney can help you understand your options and the best ways in which to structure your estate to avoid as many additional taxes as possible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Do I need an estate planning lawyer?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While there are many websites that promote do-it-yourself wills and estate planning, this is not always the right avenue for everyone. In fact, in most cases, it is best to talk through your goals with an attorney. Only an experienced, knowledgeable lawyer will be able to utilize all types of estate planning tools, such as wills, trusts, powers of attorney, advance health care directives and more, to your benefit. Without an attorney, your documents may not be legally binding and may not maximize the protection of your assets.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What do I do if I own a business?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is essential to have a plan in place that describes how the business is to be handled in the event of your death. This can be&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/business-transactions/business-succession-planning/\">achieved through business succession planning</a>, which details your wishes for the business, who is to take over, the situations in which the business may be sold and other particulars.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Estate Planning FAQs','','publish','closed','closed','','estate-planning-faqs','','','2023-10-10 21:29:42','2023-10-10 21:29:42','',20,'http://elefflaw.local/?page_id=39',1,'page','',0);
