ishes for the business, who is to take over, the situations in which the business may be sold and other particulars.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Estate Planning FAQs','','inherit','closed','closed','','39-revision-v1','','','2023-10-08 19:06:01','2023-10-08 19:06:01','',39,'http://elefflaw.local/?p=40',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (41,1,'2023-10-08 19:09:41','2023-10-08 19:09:41','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">ESTATE PLANNING TO PROTECT YOUR ASSETS AND PROVIDE GUIDANCE IN THE FUTURE</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With offices in Bethesda, Silver Spring, Maryland, and Washington, D.C.,&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group&nbsp;provides comprehensive legal counsel in matters of estate and incapacity planning, and estate administration (probate).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With more than 40 years of experience,&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;is well-qualified to offer legal guidance to document your choices and protect your familys assets.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">A Practical Approach To Estate Planning</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A well-prepared estate plan may include a will as well as trusts,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/power-of-attorney/\">powers of attorney and advance medical directives</a>, depending on your needs and priorities. If your estate is more complex, it may be wise to consider the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/business-transactions/business-succession-planning/\">future of business interests</a>&nbsp;with an emphasis on business succession planning or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/high-net-worth-estates/\">accommodating high net-worth estates</a>&nbsp;with advanced tax planning.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Susan Eleff&nbsp;and her team help clients keep the money theyve earned by providing practical legal counsel. Their hallmark is protecting their clients interests with a tailored approach. One size does not fit all in estate planning, and the firm does not burden clients or their budgets with more legal services than they need.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;as your estate planning lawyer, the process begins with a questionnaire and her instructions to spend no more than five minutes filling it out. After you complete the confidential questionnaire, you will meet by telephone or in the office to discuss your needs to allow Ms. Eleff and her team to begin crafting an estate plan to accomplish your goals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Depending on the details of your estate,&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;may recommend a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/wills/\">simple will</a>&nbsp;to direct the distribution of assets. If appropriate, she may suggest a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/trusts/\">revocable trust</a>&nbsp;to minimize the probate process. When there is a disabled loved one in the family, she will discuss whether a special needs trust is the right document to provide you with peace of mind that he or she will be well-provided for in your absence. Special provisions may be appropriate in situations with blended families or unmarried domestic partners. High net worth estates provide additional opportunities to minimize estate taxes while preserving stepped up basis and may include considerations for life insurance, family limited partnerships or asset protection measures.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whether you need just one estate planning document or a suite of documents,&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group&nbsp;will help you construct a customized and practical estate plan that protects your interests and those of your loved ones.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The firm also assists with issues that arise after the death of a loved one, as their estate proceeds through the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/probate/\">probate and estate administration processes</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Learn More About Estate Planning In A Free Initial Consultation</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you would like to begin the estate planning process or discuss your concerns with&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group, please call&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:+1-800-765-2662\">800-765-2662</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/contact/\">fill out this form</a>. Consultations are free with certain limitations. The firm serves clients throughout Montgomery County, Prince Georges County and northern Virginia.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bethesda Estate Planning Lawyer</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Rating:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;5 / 5 stars</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Rated By</strong>&nbsp;Google User<br><em>Susan Eleff&nbsp;is a great Estate/Trust lawyer. Her dedication and compassion to her clients and wealth of knowledge is superior. I would highly recommend her for all of your needs.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->','Estate Planning and Probate','','inherit','closed','closed','','20-revision-v1','','','2023-10-08 19:09:41','2023-10-08 19:09:41','',20,'http://elefflaw.local/?p=41',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (42,1,'2023-10-08 19:10:40','2023-10-08 19:10:40','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">SKILLED LEGAL COUNSEL FOR YOUR HIGH NET WORTH ESTATE OR SPECIAL SITUATION</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Eleff Law Group&nbsp;has decades of experience assisting numerous families throughout Maryland in transferring assets to future generations. Planning for the most efficient transfer of wealth from one generation to the next requires an in-depth knowledge of state and federal estate tax laws. The firm has Maryland office locations in Bethesda and Silver Spring, as well as an office in Washington, D.C.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Susan Eleff&nbsp;and her legal team work with high net worth clients to create&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/\">strategic estate plans</a>&nbsp;for high net worth individuals who need to protect their family wealth and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/business-transactions/business-succession-planning/\">business interests</a>&nbsp;while limiting tax exposure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Estate Planning Tools For Tax Planning</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Susan Eleff&nbsp;and her team implement plans that both minimize taxes and minimize changes in lifestyle for you and your heirs. A well-designed plan will utilize available gift, estate and inheritance tax exemptions, while preserving what is known as the step up in basis of assets upon death. The following are several strategies&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group&nbsp;may recommend and draft for clients, depending on their specific circumstances:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Family limited partnerships:&nbsp;</strong>A family partnership or limited liability company is usually composed of related family members who own discrete interests in a pool of assets. FLPs are typically created by parents and grandparents to transfer family businesses or other investments to the next generations. FLPs provide significant estate tax and federal gift tax benefits when coupled with valuation discounts, which take into account marketability and control characteristics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Life insurance trusts:&nbsp;</strong>If properly structured and maintained, proceeds of policies of life insurance&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/trusts/\">owned by a trust</a>&nbsp;may be excluded from the estate of the decedent, making those proceeds tax free both to the estate and the trust beneficiaries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Asset protection:</strong>&nbsp;Spendthrift provisions in a trust can shield assets from an heirs creditors and may keep them from being deemed marital assets in an heirs divorce. Certain irrevocable asset protection trusts may allow a grantor to have limited control over the assets while remaining insulated from creditor burdens.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Qualified personal residence trusts (QPRTs):&nbsp;</strong>A grantor-retained interest trust can be used to transfer a grantors residence out of his estate at a low gift tax value, allowing the grantor to live in his home for a number of years, rent free, with his remainder beneficiaries becoming fully vested in their interest at a certain point in time. By complying with certain IRS provisions, the transfer of the residence to the trust constitutes a completed gift value determined by statute, allowing the residence and future appreciation to be excluded from the grantors estate if he survives the term of the trust.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Qualified domestic trusts (QDOTs):</strong>&nbsp;A QDOT is a very specific trust designed to address the estate tax situation that arises when the spouse of a non-US citizen dies while leaving significant assets to a noncitizen surviving spouse. Noncitizen surviving spouses do not qualify for the federal estate tax marital deduction. With a QDOT, the assets can go into the trust upon the grantors death, with the surviving noncitizen spouse as a trust beneficiary. When that spouse passes away, the assets will go to the next beneficiaries named in the trust, with estate taxes deferred until the surviving spouses death.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A well-conceived and well-drafted estate plan does more than direct assets to beneficiaries. Your estate plan should also take into account the need to distribute assets to the desired recipients quickly, minimize taxes and provide an orderly and efficient transfer of business interests.&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;and her lawyer will help you navigate these issues and many others in order to efficiently and effectively pass your wealth down to the next generation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Learn More About Estate Planning, Tax Savings And Asset Preservation</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To discuss the estate planning and tax issues surrounding your high net worth estate please contact&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group&nbsp;for a *free 15-minute in-person or telephone initial consultation. Please call&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:+1-800-765-2662\">800-765-2662</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/contact/\">fill out this form</a>&nbsp;to schedule your consultation.The firm represents clients throughout the Montgomery County, Prince Georges County and northern Virginia.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>*Certain limitations may apply.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','High Net Worth Estates And Other Special Situations','','inherit','closed','closed','','35-revision-v1','','','2023-10-08 19:10:40','2023-10-08 19:10:40','',35,'http://elefflaw.local/?p=42',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (43,1,'2023-10-08 19:11:03','2023-10-08 19:11:03','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">WHAT IS A POWER OF ATTORNEY?</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Powers of attorney are very important estate planning tools. These documents allow the person executing the power of attorney, known as the principal, to designate someone he or she trusts, known as the agent or attorney, to handle certain situations on the principals behalf, in certain matters such as:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Financial accounts</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Real estate</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Digital assets</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Health care</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A power of attorney may be drafted to take effect immediately once signed, or alternatively, upon the occurrence of certain circumstances, such as disability, in which case it is referred to as a springing power of attorney. Powers of attorney that remain effective after disability are considered durable, but that durability terminates upon the death of the principal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Marylands Power Of Attorney Requirements</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Maryland law requires that financial powers of attorney signed after October 1, 2010, be notarized and include the signature of two adult witnesses (one of whom may be the notary). Health care powers of attorney need not be notarized, and in Maryland, a copy of a health care power of attorney is as effective as the original for all purposes. As with a will or trust, the principal signing a power of attorney must be legally competent at the time he or she executes the document.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to best meet your needs, it is important to choose the right type of power of attorney and ensure it will be implemented properly.&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group, is an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/\">estate planning</a>&nbsp;firm with decades of experience and has Maryland offices in Bethesda and Silver Spring, as well as a location Washington, D.C. Attorney&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;and her legal team will listen to your concerns and provide legal solutions that fit your needs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Types Of Power Of Attorney</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Forms of power of attorney in Maryland include:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Statutory personal financial power of attorney:&nbsp;</strong>This document authorizes a person whom you select as your agent, broad control over your financial and business affairs. It may also contain the principals preferences of a guardian of his or her person, or his estate, if appointment of a guardian is warranted. Third parties, such as banks, are required to accept statutory personal financial powers of attorney or face civil liability for the principals attorney fees.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Statutory limited power of attorney:&nbsp;</strong>This document is similar to the statutory personal financial power of attorney, but allows the principal to select which specific powers he or she is delegating to the agent.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Supplemental personal financial power of attorney:&nbsp;</strong>This is a document to cover certain financial or other matters not included in a Maryland statutory financial power of attorney.&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;recommends a supplemental power of attorney to cover acts such as running a business, continuing a program of gifting, and taking control of digital assets or other matters absent from the statutory form.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Advance medical directive:&nbsp;</strong>This is a health care power of attorney that names an agent to make health care decisions when the principal is unable to do so, and may also include the principals preferences for his or her care, HIPAA authorizations for access to medical care documentation, donation of body or body parts upon death of the principal and funeral arrangements.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Rescinding Or Revoking A Power Of Attorney</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All powers of attorney are deemed rescinded by the principals death. When competent, a principal may also voluntarily revoke a financial power of attorney by a subsequently executed document, duly witnessed and notarized. A later executed advance medical directive replaces and revokes one with a prior date.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Schedule Your Free Legal Consultation</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are considering appointing someone to handle your financial affairs or make health care decisions on your behalf contact&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group.&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;and her team will provide you with competent legal counsel to help you accomplish your goals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To discuss powers of attorney, or other estate planning needs or concerns, please call&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:+1-800-765-2662\">800-765-2662</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/contact/\">fill out this form</a>&nbsp;to schedule a free initial telephone or in-person consultation of up to 15 minutes; certain limitations may apply. The firm handles cases in Montgomery County, Prince Georges County and throughout northern Virginia.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Power of Attorney','','inherit','closed','closed','','22-revision-v1','','','2023-10-08 19:11:03','2023-10-08 19:11:03','',22,'http://elefflaw.local/?p=43',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (44,1,'2023-10-08 19:11:50','2023-10-08 19:11:50','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">USING TRUSTS STRATEGICALLY TO ACHIEVE YOUR GOALS</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is a commonly held misconception that trusts and trust funds are only for the wealthy. Well-drafted and executed trusts are very useful tools for families and individuals of a variety of financial backgrounds.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What is a trust? A trust, also called a living trust, is a legal arrangement that gives a trustee authority to hold assets on behalf of your beneficiaries. A trust allows you to decide how and when your beneficiaries can access the assets.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Susan Eleff, Attorney at Law, is a highly respected estate planning attorney with more than 40 years of legal experience. At her law firm,&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group, she helps people determine whether and how trusts should be included in their estate plans. The firm has Maryland office locations in Bethesda and Silver Spring, in addition to an office in Washington, D.C., from which they serve clients throughout Montgomery County, Prince Georges County and northern Virginia.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you become a client at&nbsp;The Eleff Law Group, the entire legal team will get to know you and strive to understand your priorities in order to learn whether a trust is the best means for you and your beneficiaries to:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Avoid or minimize&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/probate/\">probate</a>&nbsp;and related expenses, allowing assets to be distributed to beneficiaries quickly and directly</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Maximize privacy with a trust that is not of public record</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Minimize taxes in certain circumstances</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Protect assets from heirs creditors</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Provide the trustor with maximum control over the distribution of the assets</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Types Of Trusts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a variety of trusts available that allow individuals and families to accomplish the above-mentioned goals and others. It is important to seek counsel from a skilled and reputable lawyer like&nbsp;Susan Eleff&nbsp;and her legal team in order to decide on the best trust solution for your needs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Eleff Law Group&nbsp;helps clients create the following types of trusts and others:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Marital trust</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bypass trust</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Intentionally defective grantor trust</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/estate-planning-and-probate/high-net-worth-estates/\">Irrevocable trust</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Irrevocable life insurance trust</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Charitable lead trust</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Charitable remainder trust</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Generation-Skipping trust</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Grantor retained annuity trust</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Special needs trust</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Qualified Terminable Interest Property Trust, also called a QTIP</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Qualified Domestic Trust, also called a QDOT</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Pets Trust</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Discuss Your Estate Planning Needs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To learn more about trusts or for help developing an estate plan, call&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:+1-800-765-2662\">800-765-2662</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.elefflaw.com/contact/\">schedule a legal consultation online</a>. Initial consultations are provided free of charge with certain limitations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Trusts','','publish','closed','closed','','trusts','','','2023-10-08 19:11:50','2023-10-08 19:11:50','',20,'http://elefflaw.local/?page_id=44',0,'page','',0);
